message.content:
Edit the following test files in /home/nick/work/picolibc_agentic/libm/machine/riscv/test/ to replace large ULP-sweep loops in `test_exhaustive_small()` with small fixed arrays. Keep the function name and signature unchanged so main() doesn't need editing. Target: <=16 emit calls per function.

For each file, I describe the current loop and the replacement. Use Edit tool to make the changes.

---

## Group A: uint64_t, step=0x10000000000, range [0,1.0], single emit_u(b)
Files: test_frexp.c, test_ilogb.c

Current loop:
```c
    for (uint64_t b = 0; b <= 0x3ff0000000000000ULL; b += 0x10000000000ULL)
        emit_u(b);
```

Replace with:
```c
    static const uint64_t vals[] = {
        0x0000000000000000ULL, /* 0.0 */
        0x3fc0000000000000ULL, /* 0.125 */
        0x3fd0000000000000ULL, /* 0.25 */
        0x3fd8000000000000ULL, /* 0.375 */
        0x3fe0000000000000ULL, /* 0.5 */
        0x3fe4000000000000ULL, /* 0.625 */
        0x3fe8000000000000ULL, /* 0.75 */
        0x3ff0000000000000ULL, /* 1.0 */
    };
    for (int i = 0; i < (int)(sizeof(vals)/sizeof(vals[0])); i++)
        emit_u(vals[i]);
```

---

## Group B: uint64_t, step=0x4000000000, range [0,1.0], single emit_u(b)
File: test_modf.c

Current loop:
```c
    for (uint64_t b = 0; b <= 0x3ff0000000000000ULL; b += 0x4000000000ULL)
        emit_u(b);
```

Replace with same 8-value array as Group A.

---

## Group C: test_fabs.c — step=0x10000000000, range [0,1.0], emits b AND b|sign
Current loop in test_fabs.c:
```c
    for (uint64_t b = 0; b <= 0x3ff0000000000000ULL; b += 0x10000000000ULL) {
        emit_u(b);
        emit_u(b | 0x8000000000000000ULL);  /* same with sign bit */
    }
```

Replace with:
```c
    static const uint64_t vals[] = {
        0x0000000000000000ULL, /* 0.0 */
        0x3fc0000000000000ULL, /* 0.125 */
        0x3fd0000000000000ULL, /* 0.25 */
        0x3fe0000000000000ULL, /* 0.5 */
