## Group J: test_pow.c — nested loop, insane size
Current loop:
```c
    for (uint64_t b = base_start; b <= base_end; b += 17179869)
        for (uint64_t e = exp_start; e <= exp_end; e += 17179869)
            emit_u(b, e);
```

Replace with a flat list of hand-picked (base, exp) pairs. First READ the file to see exact variable names and context, then replace the entire body of test_exhaustive_small() with:
```c
    static const uint64_t bases[] = {
        0x3ff0000000000000ULL, /* 1.0 */
        0x3ff4000000000000ULL, /* 1.25 */
        0x3ff8000000000000ULL, /* 1.5 */
        0x3ffc000000000000ULL, /* 1.75 */
        0x4000000000000000ULL, /* 2.0 */
    };
    static const uint64_t exps[] = {
        0x0000000000000000ULL, /* 0.0 */
        0x3fd0000000000000ULL, /* 0.25 */
        0x3fe0000000000000ULL, /* 0.5 */
        0x3fe8000000000000ULL, /* 0.75 */
        0x3ff0000000000000ULL, /* 1.0 */
    };
    for (int i = 0; i < (int)(sizeof(bases)/sizeof(bases[0])); i++)
        for (int j = 0; j < (int)(sizeof(exps)/sizeof(exps[0])); j++)
            emit_u(bases[i], exps[j]);
```

